<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-55f8ebc805e65b5b71ddafdae390e3be2bcd69af">Description</h2>
The Wheel of Time series would work very well with ToME, I think.  It would replace the wilderness, monsters, and magic system.  Also, some new appropriate reaces and classes should be added.  The final boss is obvious, as is the secondary one. <h2 id="head-6a176af0e3541b91734625dec4f3b8292439dd1d">Ideas</h2>
First of all, take all the spells and redistribute them as new skills.  Either devide them up into the five uses of the One Power (Earth, Air, Fire, Water, and Spirit) or subdivide them into Talents which would be skills falling under these five.  Also, just like in the books, many spells would take a combination of skills from more than one of the five uses.  This means you would have to have certain levels in more than one to use the spell in the first place, and the power of the spell would be calculated from all the necessary types. <p>
Also add a new skill: Dagger Concealment, since so many characters in the books have the skill to hide seeminly unlimited quantities of daggers under their clothes to fling at unsuspecting enemies or to wield in emergencies. 
</p>
<p>
A few new appropriate classes:    
</p>
<p>
Spell users: Aes Sedai, Asha'man, Wilders, Wind Walkers, and Wise Ones 
</p>
<p>
Warrior:  Wolf Friend, Warder 
</p>
<p>
Rogue:  Gambler, Gleeman  (Both feature Dagger Concealment) 
</p>
<h3 id="head-ff11f0da0a4cd245270f188d8a7299b4084d0328">Chatter</h3>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: What about Ogier as new race and Warder as new class? Should Aiel and Tinker be new races ? <p>
<a class="nonexistent" href="./CatwhoWalksbyhimself">CatwhoWalksbyhimself</a>:  Definitely.  Since most of the "good" races are human, they should be main races rather than subraces.  I just forgot to mention Warders.  Could also have Wetlander, Half-man, Grey Man, Sea Folk--can't remember the rest.  Since I am working on Narnia ToME, I have no plans to make this any time soon, so some one else can feel free if they like.  Another nice thing about it is that Robert Jordan seems to freely give permission to freeware projects like this to those who actually ask him.  I know of at least one MUD and forum-based RPG with his permission. 
</p>
<p>
Shadus: Could also add mercenary and borderlander as warrior classes. 
</p>
